Eastern Platinum Ltd. (ELR)  dropped to
the lowest since Sept. 13 after saying production at its
Crocodile River Mine fell to 25,387 ounces in the three months
through March compared with 32,752 ounces in the previous
quarter.  The stock lost 49 cents, or 5.2 percent, to 8.91 rand at
9:30 a.m. in Johannesburg.  The company didnâ€™t immediately specify whether the
production was for platinum or platinum group metals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
